SixtyFourSwitcher will run under Mac OS X 10.4 ("Tiger") or 10.5 ("Leopard"), but it won't do anything under those versions of the OS, because they didn't ship with 64-bit kernels, and there's no way to get a 64-bit kernel to work with those OS versions. It will also run on Macs with 32-bit CPUs (which were the Core Solo and the original Core Duo), but once again, it won't do anything there.\
\
SixtyFourSwitcher will not run on PowerPC-based Macs at all, since it would serve no function on PPC-based Macs. Apple has never shipped a 64-bit kernel for PowerPC Macs, and most likely never will.\
