\ul How to use\ulnone \
\
When you first enter the preference pane, you should see a radio button allowing you to switch the kernel that is used on startup. By default, the selected kernel will be the one you are currently using, or will use after restarting.\
\
As with other preference panes, you'll also probably need to unlock the pane at startup using an administrator password. You do this the same way you do it in every other preference pane.\
\
